%%TITLE: CacheGuard: Detecting Stale and Poisoned Tool Caches in Agent Workflows
%%AUTHORS: Hana Okafor; Lars Meier
%%VENUE: Symposium on Secure AI Systems
%%YEAR: 2026
%%TOPIC: tool cache integrity and freshness validation
%%ABSTRACT_START
CacheGuard analyzes how stale tool results and poisoned summary caches affect autonomous agent decisions. It introduces cache provenance tags, freshness checks, and fallback strategies for high-impact workflow steps.
%%ABSTRACT_END
1 Overview
Tool outputs are often cached to save time, but stale or poisoned caches can cause agents to select unsafe actions. CacheGuard proposes a lightweight verification layer for cached observations.
